This paper deals with image fusion techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.MM). The paper also discusses analytical techniques for evaluating the quality of the fused image, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with image manipulation and enhancement.
